<section>
  <h2>6) Fuentes y normas (con enlaces)</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>NRF — <em>National Retail Security Survey 2023</em> (promedio 1,6% FY2022). <span class="ref"><a href="https://nrf.com/research/national-retail-security-survey-2023" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ficha</a></span> · <span class="ref"><a href="https://nrf.com/media-center/press-releases/shrink-accounted-over-112-billion-industry-losses-2022-according-nrf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Comunicado de prensa</a></span></li>
    <li>Deskera — <em>What is Inventory Shrinkage…</em> (ideal 1–2%). <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.deskera.com/blog/inventory-shrinkage/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artículo</a></span></li>
    <li>NIST — <em>Handbook 44 (2024) §5.50 Fabric-Measuring Devices</em> (tolerancias de medición). <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.nist.gov/pml/owm/nist-handbook-44-2024" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Índice</a></span> · <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.nist.gov/document/nist-handbook-44-2024-section-550-fabric-measuring-devices-pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a></span></li>
    <li>ES 6731:2021 — <em>Specification for tolerances of Knitted Fabrics</em> (±2% largo; 0 a +25 mm ancho; ±5% GSM). <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.ethiostandards.org/sites/default/files/2021-01/13%20Specification%20for%20tolerances%20of%20Knitted%20Fabrics.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a></span> · Referencia a <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.astm.org/d3887-96.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ASTM D3887</a></span></li>
    <li>ISO 22198:2006 — <em>Textiles — Fabrics — Determination of width and length</em> (método de medición en estado relajado). <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/40768.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ficha ISO</a></span></li>
    <li>ISO 5077:2007 — <em>Dimensional change in washing and drying</em> (ensayo de encogimiento). <span class="ref"><a href="https://cdn.standards.iteh.ai/samples/41877/ffcaa2fb92e54cdc88dd679a4f68f732/ISO-5077-2007.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF</a></span></li>
    <li>AATCC TM135 — <em>Dimensional Changes of Fabrics after Home Laundering</em>. <span class="ref"><a href="https://members.aatcc.org/store/tm135/543/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ficha</a></span></li>
    <li>Alison Hoenes — <em>Acceptable fabric shrinkage percentages</em> (≤5% tolerable; ideal &lt;3%). <span class="ref"><a href="https://alisonhoenes.com/email/acceptable-fabric-shrinkage-percentages/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artículo</a></span></li>
    <li>Online Clothing Study — <em>Control of fabric shrinkage…</em> (planos 2–4%, punto 3–8%, stretch 10–18%). <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.onlineclothingstudy.com/2015/04/control-fabric-shrinkage-in-garment.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artículo</a></span></li>
    <li>Cotton Incorporated — <em>Fabric Defects Classification (Four-Point System)</em>. <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.cottoninc.com/quality-products/textile-resources/fabric-defects-classification/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Recurso</a></span></li>
    <li>Unleashed — <em>Cycle Counting &gt; 97% accuracy</em>. <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.unleashedsoftware.com/blog/inventory-cycle-count/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artículo</a></span></li>
    <li>CadreTech — <em>Warehouse KPIs</em> (objetivo 97–98% exactitud). <span class="ref"><a href="https://www.cadretech.com/blog/warehouse-kpis/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Artículo</a></span></li>
  </ol>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>7) Qué monitorear desde mañana</h2>
  <div class="grid cols-3">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Checklist — recepción</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Medición en estado relajado (ISO 22198).</li>
        <li>Verificación quincenal del contador (NIST HB 44) con cinta patrón.</li>
        <li>Registrar “splices”, daños de orillo y mermas no utilizables.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Checklist — inventario</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Cycle counting ABC (A semanal / B mensual / C trimestral).</li>
        <li>Reporte de <span class="kbd">ajustes por causa</span> (M/D/U/P) y por proveedor.</li>
        <li>Tablero: <strong>Shrink % mensual</strong>, <strong>Exactitud %</strong>, <strong>Top 10 desvíos</strong>.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Checklist — calidad</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensayo de encogimiento por artículo/partida (ISO 5077 / AATCC 135).</li>
        <li>Inspección Four-Point por rollo crítico (color oscuro, estampado, elastizado).</li>
        <li>Política de aceptación y nota de débito al proveedor cuando aplique.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

